1. What is the difference between more and less command
more and less commands in Linux are used to view large files page by page in the terminal. They are called paging commands. However, less is more powerful and flexible than more.
more command displays file content one screen at a time and allows limited
Limitations
Cannot easily scroll backward
Limited navigation
Less interactive
less command is an improved version of more with more features. - Scroll to navigate to pages.
The more command displays file content page by page but allows mostly forward navigation.
The less command is an advanced pager that allows both forward and backward navigation, searching, and better control when viewing large files.

2.In the vi editor, how to delete the character in forward direction?

Come out of insert mode and stay in command mode, then click on x - for single character - It helps u to delete character.

For multiple character - 5x, 4x, 3x etc

3.In the vi editor, how to delete the character in backward direction

Come out of insert mode and stay in command mode, then click on X - for single character in backward direction- It helps u to delete character.

For multiple character - 5X, 4X, 3X etc


